OL,3,CWelsh government accepts 'need' to
OL,4,Cimprove guidance on teaching reading
OL,6,FIn one recent Estyn report, an
OL,7,Finspector noted that "younger pupils
OL,8,Fquickly develop a good understanding
OL,9,Fof letter sounds and use picture cues
OL,10,Fto develop their early reading skills."
OL,12,FCurriculum for Wales guidance also
OL,13,Fsays pupils should use "context and
OL,14,Fpictures" to help them understand what
OL,15,Fthey read.
OL,17,FThe Welsh government disputes that
OL,18,Fthis promotes the use of "cueing"
OL,19,Fstrategies to tackle unfamiliar words,
OL,20,Fbut now admits that its guidance
OL,21,F"needs to be clarified".
