OL,3,CWelsh government accepts 'need' to
OL,4,Cimprove guidance on teaching reading
OL,6,FOn Thursday, a Welsh government
OL,7,Fspokeswoman told ITV News:
OL,9,F"We accept there are places in our
OL,10,Fguidance where the importance of
OL,11,Fphonics needs to be more explicit and
OL,12,Fwhere wording needs to be clarified
OL,13,Faround the use of picture cues."
OL,15,FThe government further clarified that
OL,16,Fit does not believe that children
OL,17,Fshould be taught to use picture cues
OL,18,Fto decode unfamiliar words.
