OL,3,CWelsh government accepts 'need' to
OL,4,Cimprove guidance on teaching reading
OL,6,FThis was the first time anyone in the
OL,7,FWelsh government has ever used the
OL,8,Fterm "synthetic phonics" in relation
OL,9,Fto guidance for schools in Wales, but
OL,10,Fthe government says that the synthetic
OL,11,Fphonics approach is specifically
OL,12,Fdescribed in the curriculum
OL,13,Fexpectations.
OL,15,FHowever, ITV News has obtained an
OL,16,Femail written by a civil servant in
OL,17,Fthe Welsh government's education
OL,18,Fdepartment in May 2024 which states
OL,19,Fusing one particular method of
OL,20,Fteaching reading would "undermine" the
OL,21,Fcurriculum.
